comments: It was clear from the beginning each colour corresponded to a relatively similar structure of the final segment of the word, and that each symbol corresponded to an equal initial segment. However, the text-to-speech modulator used in this study was incredibly subpar. The TTS actively harmed learning new words, because it pronounced each colour variation almost exactly the same. I do not know if that was the intent of the study or a side effect, but I found it easier to memorize if I tried to actively ignore the voice.
